This paper focuses on the impact of imputation methods on classification models, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper specifically deals with missing features, which is a problem that falls under the category of data preprocessing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions the use of MLP and XGBT, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE), respectively.
